name: KATELIJNE

meaning: From Japanese 順 (jun) meaning "obedience" or 純 (jun) meaning "pure" combined with 子 (ko) meaning "child". Other combinations of kanji characters are also possible.
name: JUNKO

meaning: From Sino-Korean 俊 (jun) meaning "talented, handsome" combined with 舒 (seo) meaning "open up, unfold, comfortable, easy" or 瑞 (seo) meaning "felicitous omen, auspicious". This name can be formed by other hanja character combinations as well.
name: JUN-SEO

meaning: Croatian and Slovak form of GEORGE.
name: JURAJ

meaning: Medieval Low German form of GEORGE.
name: JURIAN

meaning: Slovene and Sorbian form of GEORGE.
name: JURIJ

meaning: From Japanese 十 (ju) meaning "ten" and 郎 (rou) meaning "son". Traditionally this name was given to the tenth son. Other combinations of kanji characters are possible as well.
name: JUROU

meaning: From an occupational surname which meant "judge, officer of justice" in Old French. This name can also be given in direct reference to the English word justice.
name: JUSTICE

meaning: Slovak feminine form of Iustinus (see JUSTIN).
name: JUSTÍNA

meaning: From the Latin name Iustinianus, which was derived from Iustinus (see JUSTIN). This was the name of a 6th-century Byzantine emperor who attempted to restore the borders of the Roman Empire.
name: JUSTINIAN

meaning: Czech feminine form of Iustinus (see JUSTIN).
name: JUSTÝNA

meaning: Probably a medieval Low German form of JUDITH. It might also derive from a Germanic name such as JUDDA.
name: JUTTA

meaning: From the Roman cognomen Iuvenalis which meant "youthful" in Latin. Juvenal was a Roman satirist of the 1st century.
name: JUVENAL

meaning: From Sino-Korean 周 (ju) meaning "circumference" combined with 元 (won) meaning "first, origin" or 媛 (won) meaning "beautiful woman". Other hanja character combinations are possible.
name: JU-WON

meaning: Derived from Sanskrit ज्योतिस् (jyotis) meaning "light". This is a transcription of both the feminine form ज्योती and the masculine form ज्योति.
name: JYOTI

meaning: From the name of a type of green gemstone found in New Zealand, meaning "sky blue" in Maori.
name: KAHURANGI

meaning: From the name of a mountain in the Himalayas which is believed to be the paradise of the Hindu god Shiva. It possibly means "crystal" in Sanskrit.
name: KAILASH

meaning: From Hawaiian kai "ocean, sea" and mana "power". It is also Hawaiian meaning "diamond", derived from the English word diamond.
name: KAIMANA

meaning: Form of CAINAN used in the Greek Old Testament.
name: KAINAN

meaning: Finnish and Estonian diminutive of KATHERINE.
name: KAISA

meaning: Means "kohl, collyrium, lotion for the eyes" in Sanskrit.
name: KAJAL

meaning: Means "the heavens" from Hawaiian ka "the" and lani "heaven, sky, royal, majesty".
name: KALANI

meaning: Means "sound, voice" from Hawaiian ka "the" and leo "sound, voice".
name: KALEO

meaning: Means "the black one" in Sanskrit. The Hindu goddess Kali is the fierce destructive form of the wife of Shiva. She is usually depicted with black skin and four arms, holding a severed head and brandishing a sword. As a personal name, it is generally masculine in India.
name: KALI

meaning: Means "servant of Kali" from the name of the Hindu goddess KALI combined with Sanskrit दास (dasa) meaning "servant". This was the name of a 4th-century Indian poet and dramatist, the author of the 'Abhijnanashakuntalam'.
name: KALIDASA

meaning: Combination of the popular name prefix Ka and LISHA.
name: KALISHA

meaning: Derived from Greek καλλος (kallos) meaning "beauty". This was the name of an Athenian who fought at Marathon who later became an ambassador to the Persians.
name: KALLIAS

meaning: Means "beautiful power", derived from the Greek elements καλλος (kallos) "beauty" and κρατος (kratos) "power".
name: KALLIKRATES

meaning: Derived from Greek καλλιστος (kallistos) meaning "most beautiful", a derivative of καλος (kalos) "beautiful". In Greek mythology Kallisto was a nymph who was loved by Zeus. She was changed into a she-bear by Hera, and subsequently became the Great Bear constellation. This was also an ancient Greek personal name.
name: KALLISTO

meaning: Means "beautiful army" from the Greek elements καλλος (kallos) "beauty" and στρατος (stratos) "army".
name: KALLISTRATE

meaning: From Greek καλος Ιωαννης (kalos Ioannes) meaning "handsome JOHN", the nickname of a 13th-century emperor of Bulgaria. He successfully defended the empire from the Fourth Crusade.
name: KALOYAN

meaning: Means "beautiful, lovely, auspicious" in Sanskrit. In the Hindu epic the 'Mahabharata' this is the name of one of the Krittikas, or Pleiades. It is also another name of the Hindu goddess Parvati.
name: KALYANI

meaning: From the Ukrainian word for a type of shrub, also called the guelder rose.
name: KALYNA

meaning: Means "love, desire" in Sanskrit. Kama is the winged Hindu god of love, the son of Lakshmi.
name: KAMA

meaning: Means "lotus" or "pale red" in Sanskrit. This is a transcription of both the feminine form कमला and the masculine form कमल. This is the name of one of the Krittikas, or Pleiades, in Hindu epic the 'Mahabharata'. It is also another name of the Hindu goddess Lakshmi.
name: KAMALA
origin: [Hinduism, Tamil, Indian, Kannada, Telugu, Hindi, Nepali]

meaning: Swahili name, likely related to QAMAR.
name: KAMARIA

meaning: Means "stone" in Bulgarian. This is a translation of the Greek name Petros.
name: KAMEN

meaning: Czech, Slovak and Polish form of CAMILLA.
name: KAMILA

meaning: Hungarian form of CAMILLA, as well as a Scandinavian variant. This is also the Hungarian word for the chamomile flower (species Matricaria chamomilla).
name: KAMILLA

meaning: Means "one that walks on four claws" in Cree. This was the name of a 19th-century Cree chief.
name: KANEONUSKATEW

meaning: From Japanese 花 (ka) meaning "flower, blossom" and 音 (non) meaning "sound". Other kanji combinations are possible as well.
name: KANON

meaning: Means "beauty" in Sanskrit. This is a transcription of both the feminine form कान्ती (another name of the Hindu goddess Lakshmi) and the masculine form कान्ति.
name: KANTI

meaning: Anglicized form of CAOLÁN. This is also the name of a type of clay.
name: KAOLIN

meaning: From Japanese 薫 (kaoru) meaning "fragrant", as well as other kanji having the same reading.
name: KAORU

meaning: Means "reddish brown" in Sanskrit, derived from कपि (kapi) "monkey". In the Hindu epic the 'Mahabharata' this is the name of a sage who founded Samkhya philosophy and is identified with the god Vishnu.
name: KAPILA

meaning: Means "the flower" or "the child" from Hawaiian ka, a definite article, and pua "flower, offspring".
name: KAPUA

meaning: Variant transcription of KARIM. A famous bearer of this name is basketball player Kareem Abdul-Jabbar (1947-).
name: KAREEM

meaning: Dutch, Czech and Slovene form of CHARLES.
name: KAREL
KARINA
origin: [Swedish, Danish, Norwegian, Polish, German, Russian, English]

meaning: German and Scandinavian form of CHARLES. This was the name of seven emperors of the Holy Roman Empire and an emperor of Austria, as well as kings of Sweden and Norway. Other famous bearers include Karl Marx (1818-1883), the German philosopher and revolutionary who laid the foundations for communism, and Karl Jaspers (1883-1969), a German existentialist philosopher.
name: KARL
origin: [German, Swedish, Norwegian, Danish, English, Finnish, Ancient Germanic]

meaning: Slovene and Croatian form of CARMEN.
name: KARMEN

meaning: Polish, Slovak and Slovene form of KARL.
name: KAROL
KAROLINA
origin: [Polish, Swedish, Norwegian, Danish, Hungarian, Slovene, Croatian, Macedonian, Lithuanian, German]

meaning: Southern Indian feminine form of KARTIK.
name: KARTHIKA

meaning: From Sanskrit कृत्तिका (krittika), the name for the constellation of the Pleiades.
name: KARTIK

meaning: English variant and Polish form of CASSANDRA.
name: KASANDRA

meaning: From the name of a holy city in India, famous for its many temples dedicated to the Hindu god Shiva. Its name is derived from Sanskrit काशि (kashi) meaning "shining".
name: KASHI

meaning: Dutch and Scandinavian form of JASPER.
name: KASPER

meaning: From Japanese 霞 (kasumi) meaning "mist". It can also come from 花 (ka) meaning "flower, blossom" combined with 澄 (sumi) meaning "clear, pure". Other kanji combinations are also possible.
name: KASUMI

meaning: Hungarian short form of KATALIN, Finnish short form of KATARIINA and Croatian short form of KATARINA.
name: KATA

meaning: Finnish and Estonian form of KATHERINE.
name: KATARIINA

meaning: From Japanese 堅 (katashi) meaning "hard, firm" or other kanji and kanji combinations which are pronounced the same way.
name: KATASHI

meaning: Diminutive of KATHERINE, often used independently. It has been used in England since the Middle Ages. This was the name of the woman who Petruchio marries and tries to tame in Shakespeare's comedy 'Taming of the Shrew' (1593). A famous bearer is the British actress Kate Winslet (1975-).
name: KATE

meaning: Dutch form of KATHERINE, used especially in Flanders.
name: KATELIJN

meaning: From the Mohawk pronunciation of KATHERINE. This was the name adopted by the 17th-century Mohawk woman Tekakwitha upon her baptism. She has been beatified by the Catholic Church.
name: KATERI

meaning: Macedonian form of KATHERINE, a Russian short form of YEKATERINA, a Bulgarian short form of EKATERINA, and a Greek variant of AIKATERINE.
name: KATERINA

meaning: English variant of KATHERINE and German variant of KATHARINA. A famous bearer was American actress Katharine Hepburn (1907-2003).
name: KATHARINE

meaning: From the Greek name Αικατερινη (Aikaterine). The etymology is debated: it could derive from the earlier Greek name ‘Εκατερινη (Hekaterine), which came from ‘εκατερος (hekateros) "each of the two"; it could derive from the name of the goddess HECATE; it could be related to Greek αικια (aikia) "torture"; or it could be from a Coptic name meaning "my consecration of your name". In the early Christian era it became associated with Greek καθαρος (katharos) "pure", and the Latin spelling was changed from Katerina to Katharina to reflect this.... [more]
name: KATHERINE

meaning: Danish and Norwegian form of KATHERINE.
name: KATHRINE

meaning: Greek and Macedonian contracted form of KATERINA. This name had a spike in popularity in America in 1972 when it was used for a newborn baby on the soap opera 'Where the Heart Is'.
name: KATINA

meaning: German, Scandinavian, Dutch and Slovene form of KATYA.
name: KATJA

meaning: German, Swedish and Estonian short form of KATHERINE.
name: KATRIN

meaning: Danish and Norwegian form of KATHERINE.
name: KATRINE

meaning: From Japanese 勝 (katsu) meaning "victory" and 雄 (o) meaning "hero, manly". Other combinations of kanji are also possible.
name: KATSUO

meaning: From Japanese 勝 (katsu) meaning "victory" and 郎 (rou) meaning "son". Different kanji characters can combine to form this name as well.
name: KATSUROU

meaning: Means "the youthful one" from Hawaiian ka, a definite article, and u'i "youth, beauty".
name: KAUI

meaning: From the name of a type of tree found in New Zealand (species Agathis australis).
name: KAURI

meaning: Possibly means "royal" in Avestan. In Persian mythology Kaveh is a blacksmith who leads a rebellion against the evil ruler Zahhak.
name: KAVEH

meaning: From a title for a a poet, meaning "wise man, sage, poet" in Sanskrit.
name: KAVI

meaning: Means "the adornment" from Hawaiian ka, a definite article, and wehi "adornment".
name: KAWEHI

meaning: From the Welsh name Cai or Cei, possibly a form of the Roman name GAIUS. Sir Kay was one of the Knights of the Round Table in Arthurian legend. He first appears in Welsh tales as a brave companion of Arthur. In later medieval tales, notably those by the 12th-century French poet Chrétien de Troyes, he is portrayed as an unrefined boor.
name: KAY  (2)

meaning: Combination of KAY  (1) and the popular name suffix la. Use of the name was greatly increased in the 1980s after the character Kayla Brady began appearing on the American soap opera 'Days of Our Lives'.
name: KAYLA  (1)

meaning: Combination of KAY  (1) and the popular name suffix leen.
name: KAYLEEN

meaning: Combination of KAY  (1) and the popular name suffix lyn.
name: KAYLYN

meaning: Czech, Slovak and Hungarian form of CASIMIR.
name: KAZIMÍR

meaning: From Japanese 一 (kazu) meaning "one" or 和 (kazu) meaning "harmony, peace" combined with 輝 (ki) meaning "brightness", 希 (ki) meaning "hope" or 樹 (ki) meaning "tree", as well as other combinations of kanji characters.
name: KAZUKI

meaning: From Japanese 一 (kazu) meaning "one" or 和 (kazu) meaning "harmony, peace" combined with 男 (o) meaning "male, man" or 夫 (o) meaning "husband, man". Other kanji combinations can also form this name.
name: KAZUO

meaning: Means "the path" from Hawaiian ke, a definite article, and ala "path".
name: KEALA

meaning: Combination of the popular name prefix Ke and ANNA.
name: KEANNA

meaning: From an Irish surname, the Anglicized form of the Gaelic Mac Aodhagáin, which means "descendant of Aodhagán". The given name Aodhagán is a double diminutive of AODH.
name: KEEGAN

meaning: From a surname which was derived from an English place name, ultimately meaning "clearing belonging to Cyhha". The Old English given name Cyhha is of unknown meaning. This name also serves as a variant of KAYLEE.
name: KEIGHLEY

meaning: From a surname which was a variant of KERR.
name: KEIR

meaning: From a Scottish surname which was originally derived from a place name, itself probably derived from the Brythonic element cet meaning "wood". This was the surname of a long line of Scottish nobles. It has been used as a given name since the 19th century.
name: KEITH

meaning: Meaning unknown, perhaps an invented name.
name: KELIA

meaning: Anglicized form of the Irish given name CEALLACH or the surname derived from it Ó Ceallaigh. As a surname, it has been borne by actor and dancer Gene Kelly (1912-1996) and actress and princess Grace Kelly (1929-1982).
name: KELLY

meaning: From the name of a Scottish river, perhaps meaning "narrow water". As a title it was borne by the Irish-Scottish physicist William Thomson, Lord Kelvin (1824-1907), who acquired his title from the river.
name: KELVIN

meaning: Possibly means "possession" in Hebrew. He is a son of Enosh and a great-grandson of Adam in the Old Testament.
name: KENAN

meaning: From a surname which comes from the name of the city of Kendale in northwest England meaning "valley on the river Kent".
name: KENDALL

meaning: From a surname which has several different origins. It could be from the Old English given names Cyneric "royal power" or Cenric "bold power", or from the Welsh name Cynwrig "chief hero". It can also be an Anglicized form of the Gaelic surname Mac Eanraig meaning "son of HENRY".
name: KENDRICK

meaning: From Japanese 健 (ken) meaning "healthy, strong" or 研 (ken) meaning "study, sharpen" combined with 一 (ichi) meaning "one". Other kanji combinations are possible.
name: KEN'ICHI

meaning: From an irish surname, an Anglicized form of Ó Cinnéidigh meaning "descendant of CENNÉTIG". The name is often given in honour of assassinated American president John F. Kennedy (1917-1963).
name: KENNEDY

meaning: Anglicized form of both COINNEACH and CINÁED. This name was borne by the Scottish king Kenneth (Cináed) mac Alpin, who united the Scots and Picts in the 9th century. It was popularized outside of Scotland by Sir Walter Scott, who used it for the hero in his novel 'The Talisman' (1825). A famous bearer was the British novelist Kenneth Grahame (1859-1932), who wrote 'The Wind in the Willows'.
name: KENNETH

meaning: From Japanese 謙 (ken) meaning "humble, modest" and 信 (shin) meaning "trust, believe". Other kanji combinations can also form this name.
name: KENSHIN

meaning: From Japanese 健 (ken) meaning "healthy, strong" and 太 (ta) meaning "thick, big", as well as other kanji combinations having the same pronunciation.
name: KENTA

meaning: From a surname which was derived from an English place name meaning either "town on the River Kenn" or "royal town" in Old English.
name: KENTON

meaning: From a surname which was derived from an English place name, of uncertain meaning.
name: KENYON

meaning: Means "the homeland" from Hawaiian ke, a definite article, and one "sand, homeland".
name: KEONE

meaning: Means "horn" or "ray of light" in Hebrew.
name: KEREN

meaning: Means "horn of antimony" in Hebrew. Antimony is a substance that was formerly used as an eye cosmetic (eyeshadow). A hollowed animal horn could have been used to store this material. Keren-Happuch is the name of the third daughter of Job in the Old Testament.
name: KEREN-HAPPUCH

meaning: From a Manx surname, a variant of the Irish surname MacDermott meaning "son of DIARMAID". Theodore Roosevelt used it for one of his sons. The name is now associated with Kermit the Frog, one of the Muppets created by puppeteer Jim Henson.
name: KERMIT

meaning: From a Scottish surname which was derived from a place name meaning "rough wet ground" in Old Norse.
name: KERR

meaning: Combination of the popular name prefix Ke and SHAWN.
name: KESHAWN

meaning: From the name of the bird of prey, ultimately derived from Old French crecelle "rattle", which refers to the sound of its cry.
name: KESTREL

meaning: Georgian form of KATAYUN. It is sometimes used as a Georgian form of KATHERINE.
name: KETEVAN

meaning: From the Old Norse name Ketill meaning "kettle, cauldron" (later also acquiring the meaning "helmet"). In old Scandinavian rituals the ketill was used to catch the blood of sacrificed animals.
name: KETIL

meaning: Possibly from a Balinese word meaning "small banana". This name is traditionally given to the fourth child.
name: KETUT

meaning: Anglicized form of the Irish name Caoimhín, derived from the older Irish Cóemgein, composed of the Old Irish elements cóem "kind, gentle, handsome" and gein "birth". Saint Caoimhín established a monastery in Glendalough, Ireland in the 6th century and is the patron saint of Dublin. It became popular in the English-speaking world outside of Ireland in the 20th century.
name: KEVIN
origin: [English, Irish, French, German, Dutch, Swedish, Norwegian, Danish]

meaning: Variant or feminine form of KEVIN.
name: KEVYN

meaning: Means "given by the cross" in Armenian.
name: KHACHATUR

meaning: Means "premature child" in Arabic. This was the name of the Prophet Muhammad's first wife and the mother of all of his children. She was a wealthy merchant and a widow when they married in the year 595. Muhammad received his first revelation 15 years after their marriage, and she was the first person to convert to Islam.
name: KHADIJA

meaning: Means "creator" in Arabic. In Islamic tradition الخليق (al-Khaliq) is one of the 99 names of Allah.
name: KHALIQ

meaning: From a title meaning "king, ruler". Its origin is Mongolian, though the word has been transmitted into many other languages.
name: KHAN

meaning: Means "good deeds" in Arabic, plural of خيرة (khayrah).
name: KHAYRAT

meaning: Means "God given" from Persian خدا (khoda) "god, lord" and داد (dad) "gave".
name: KHODADAD

meaning: Modern Persian form of Avestan Hvare Khshaeta meaning "shining sun". In Zoroastrianism this was the name of a Yazata (or angel) who was associated with the sun.
name: KHURSHID

meaning: From a title meaning "master, owner" in Persian. It is not generally used as a name itself.
name: KHWAJA

meaning: Means "king, foundation, symbol of pride" in Persian.
name: KIAN  (1)

meaning: From Japanese 吉 (kichi) meaning "good luck" and 郎 (rou) meaning "son". Other kanji combinations are also possible.
name: KICHIROU

meaning: Means "lily of the valley" in Finnish.
name: KIELO

meaning: Variant of KIARA influenced by the spelling of SIERRA.
name: KIERRA

meaning: Diminutive of names beginning with or containing the sound K.
name: KIKI

meaning: Latinate form of KATHERINE. Shakespeare used this name in his play 'Taming of the Shrew' (1593).
name: KATHERINA

meaning: Finnish and Estonian diminutive of KATARIINA and a Hungarian diminutive of KATALIN.
name: KATI

meaning: Croatian, Slovene and Hungarian diminutive of KATHERINE.
name: KATICA

meaning: German diminutive of KATHARINA, a Hungarian diminutive of KATALIN and a Dutch diminutive of CATHARINA.
name: KATINKA

meaning: Variant of CATRIONA. It is also a German, Swedish and Dutch contracted form of KATHERINE.
name: KATRINA

meaning: From Japanese 勝 (katsu) meaning "victory", as well as other kanji having the same pronunciation.
name: KATSU

meaning: Means "princess", ultimately from Sanskrit कुमारी (kumari) meaning "girl". This surname was assigned to all female Sikhs in 1699 by Guru Gobind Singh. It is now used as a surname or a middle name by most female Sikhs. The male equivalent is Singh.
name: KAUR

meaning: Means "of the Kosala people" in Sanskrit. Kosala was an ancient Indian kingdom that was at its most powerful in the 6th century BC. In Hindu legend Kausalya is the name of the mother of the hero Rama.
name: KAUSALYA

meaning: From the name of the Kaveri River in southern India.
name: KAVERI

meaning: Means "poor man" or "lean man" in Cree. This was the name of a 19th-century Cree chief.
name: KAWACATOOSE

meaning: Short form of KATHERINE and other names beginning with K.
name: KAY  (1)

meaning: Combination of KAY  (1) and the popular name suffix lee.
name: KAYLEE

meaning: Variant of KAYLEE. This is also a common Anglicized form of the Gaelic word ceilidh, a traditional social gathering and dance.
name: KAYLEIGH

meaning: From Japanese 和 (kazu) meaning "harmony, peace" or 一 (kazu) meaning "one" combined with 枝 (e) meaning "branch" or 恵 (e) meaning "favour, benefit". Other combinations of kanji characters can potentially form this name.
name: KAZUE

meaning: From Japanese 一 (kazu) meaning "one" or 和 (kazu) meaning "harmony, peace" combined with 子 (ko) meaning "child". This name can also be formed from other kanji combinations.
name: KAZUKO

meaning: Means "the fire" from Hawaiian ke, a definite article, and ahi "fire".
name: KEAHI

meaning: Means "the loved one" from Hawaiian ke, a definite article, and aloha "love".
name: KEALOHA

meaning: Means "the cool breeze" from Hawaiian ke, a definite article, and anu "coolness".
name: KEANU

meaning: From a surname which was derived from a place name meaning "shed town" in Old English.
name: KEATON

meaning: From an Irish surname, an Anglicized form of Ó Caoimh meaning "descendant of CAOMH".
name: KEEFE

meaning: Anglicized form of CAOILFHIONN, sometimes used as a masculine name.
name: KEELAN

meaning: From an Irish surname, an Anglicized form of Ó Caolaidhe meaning "descendant of Caoladhe". The given name Caoladhe is derived from the Gaelic word caol "slender".
name: KEELY

meaning: Dutch diminutive of CORNELIUS. A notable bearer was the Dutch painter Kees van Dongen (1877-1968).
name: KEES

meaning: From Japanese 慶 (kei) meaning "celebrate", 敬 (kei) meaning "respect", 啓 (kei) meaning "open, begin" or 恵 (kei) meaning "favour, benefit" combined with 子 (ko) meaning "child". Other kanji combinations are possible.
name: KEIKO

meaning: Variant of KIRA  (2). This spelling was popularized by British actress Keira Knightley (1985-).
name: KEIRA

meaning: Recent coinage, possibly invented, possibly based on KEZIAH.
name: KEISHA

meaning: Means "the warrior" from Hawaiian ke, a definite article, and koa "warrior, koa tree".
name: KEKOA

meaning: Possibly derived from Old Norse kildr meaning "a spring".
name: KELDA

meaning: From an English surname which is derived from town names in Lincolnshire. It may mean "Cenel's island", from the Old English name Cenel "fierce" in combination with eg "island".
name: KELSEY

meaning: Turkish form of KAMAL  (1). This was the second name, acquired in his youth, of Mustafa Kemal Atatürk (1881-1938), the founder of modern Turkey.
name: KEMAL

meaning: From a surname derived from Middle English kempe meaning "champion, athlete, warrior".
name: KEMP

meaning: From Japanese 健 (ken) meaning "healthy, strong" or other kanji which are pronounced the same way.
name: KEN  (2)

meaning: Means "YAHWEH establishes" in Hebrew. This was the name of two minor Old Testament characters.
name: KENANIAH

meaning: From a surname which was a variant of KENDALL.
name: KENDAL

meaning: Feminine form of KEN  (1) or KENDRICK.
name: KENDRA

meaning: From the Old English name Cenhelm, which was composed of the elements cene "bold, keen" and helm "helmet". Saint Kenelm was a 9th-century martyr from Mercia, where he was a member of the royal family. The name was occasionally used during the Middle Ages, but has since become rare.
name: KENELM

meaning: From Japanese 研 (ken) meaning "study, sharpen" and 二 (ji) meaning "two", as well as other combinations of kanji characters.
name: KENJI

meaning: From a surname which was derived from the Old English given names CYNEWEARD or CYNEHEARD.
name: KENNARD

meaning: From a surname which was originally derived from Kent, the name of a county in England, which may be derived from a Brythonic word meaning "coastal district".
name: KENT

meaning: Possibly means "chief lord" in Gaelic. This was the name of a 6th-century saint from Glasgow.
name: KENTIGERN

meaning: From the name of the African country. The country is named for Mount Kenya, which in the Kikuyu language is called Kere Nyaga meaning "mountain of whiteness". It has been used as a given name in the English-speaking world since the 1960s.
name: KENYA

meaning: From the name of the Irish county, called Ciarraí in Irish Gaelic, which means "CIAR's people".
name: KERRY

meaning: Combination of the popular name prefix Ke and SHAUN.
name: KESHAUN

meaning: Means "to cope" in Lithuanian. This was the name of a 14th-century ruler of Lithuania.
name: KĘSTUTIS

meaning: Means "incense" in Hebrew. In the Old Testament she is Abraham's wife after Sarah dies.
name: KETURAH

meaning: From the Hebrew name קְצִיעָה (Qetzi'ah) meaning "cassia, cinnamon", from the name of the spice tree. In the Old Testament she is a daughter of Job.
name: KEZIAH

meaning: Variant transcription of KHADIJA. This corresponds more closely with the Egyptian Arabic pronunciation of the name.
name: KHADIGA

meaning: Means "eternal", derived from Arabic خلد (khalada) "to last forever". This name was borne by a 7th-century Islamic military leader, Khalid ibn-al-Walid.

meaning: Means "successor, caliph" in Arabic. The title caliph was given to the successors of the Prophet Muhammad, originally elected by the Islamic populace.
name: KHALIFA

meaning: Derived from the Turkic title Khan which means "ruler, leader" combined with the high Ottoman military rank pasha.
name: KHANPASHA

meaning: Possibly from Turkic katun meaning "lady, woman".
name: KHATUNA

In her novel 'Show Boat' (1926) Edna Ferber used it for a female character who was born on the Mississippi River and was named from the initials of the states Kentucky, Illinois and Mississippi. meaning: From the Hebrew name לֵאָה (Le'ah) which was probably derived from the Hebrew word לְאָה (le'ah) meaning "weary". Alternatively it might derive from a Chaldean name meaning "mistress" or "ruler" in Akkadian. In the Old Testament Leah is the first wife of Jacob and the mother of seven of his children. Jacob's other wife was Leah's sister Rachel. Although this name was used by Jews in the Middle Ages, it was not typical as an English Christian name until after the Protestant Reformation, being common among the Puritans.
name: LEAH

meaning: Latinized form of the Greek name Λεανδρος (Leandros), derived from λεων (leon) meaning "lion" and ανηρ (aner) meaning "man" (genitive ανδρος). In Greek legend Leander was the lover of Hero. Every night he swam across the Hellespont to meet her, but on one occasion he was drowned when a storm arose. When Hero saw his dead body she threw herself into the waters and perished.
name: LEANDER
