name: TESNI

meaning: Possibly derived from an Illyrian word or title meaning "queen". This was the name of a 3rd-century BC Illyrian queen.
name: TEUTA

meaning: From a nickname which denoted a person who came from the state of Texas. A famous bearer was the American animator Tex Avery (1908-1980), real name Frederick, who was born in Texas.
name: TEX

meaning: Form of THADDEUS used in most English versions of the New Testament.
name: THADDAEUS

meaning: From Θαδδαιος (Thaddaios), the Greek form of the Aramaic name Thaddai. It is possibly derived from a word meaning "heart", but it may in fact be an Aramaic form of a Greek name such as Θεοδωρος (see THEODORE). In the Gospel of Matthew, Thaddaeus is listed as one of the twelve apostles, though elsewhere in the New Testament his name is omitted and Jude's appears instead. It is likely that the two names refer to the same person.
name: THADDEUS

meaning: Possibly means "bandage" in Greek. This was the name of a companion of Alexander the Great. It was also borne by a 4th-century saint from Alexandria, a wealthy socialite who became a Christian convert. She has been a popular subject of art and literature, including an 1891 novel by Anatole France and an 1894 opera by Jules Massenet.
name: THAÏS

meaning: Derived from Greek θαλλω (thallo) meaning "to blossom". This was the name of a 6th-century BC Greek philosopher and mathematician.
name: THALES

meaning: Modern Greek short form of ATHANASIOS.
name: THANASIS

meaning: From the Scottish and English noble title, which was originally from Old English thegn.
name: THANE

meaning: From the ancient Greek name Θεοκλεια (Theokleia), which meant "glory of God" from the Greek elements θεος (theos) meaning "god" and κλεος (kleos) meaning "glory". This was the name of a 1st-century saint, appearing (as Θεκλα) in the apocryphal 'Acts of Paul and Thecla'. The story tells how Thecla listens to Paul speak about the virtues of chastity and decides to remain a virgin, angering both her mother and her suitor.
name: THEKLA

meaning: Latinized form of Tielo (see TILO). A famous bearer was jazz musician Thelonious Monk (1917-1982).
name: THELONIUS

meaning: Latinized form of the Greek name Θεμιστοκλης (Themistokles) meaning "glory of the law", from θεμις (themis) "law of nature, divine law" (genitive θεμιστος) and κλεος (kleos) "glory". This was the name of an Athenian statesman and general who was victorious over the Persians in the Battle of Salamis.
name: THEMISTOCLES

meaning: Short form of THEODORE, THEOBALD, and other names that begin with Theo.
name: THEO

meaning: Latinized form of Θεοκριτος (Theokritos), a Greek name which meant "judge of god" from θεος (theos) "god" and κριτης (krites) "judge, critic". This was the name of a 3rd-century BC Greek poet.
name: THEOCRITUS

meaning: Germanic name composed of the elements theud "people" and war "vigilant, cautious".
name: THEODOAR

meaning: From a Germanic name meaning "ruler of the people", derived from the elements theud "people" and ric "power, ruler". It was notably borne by Theodoric the Great, a 6th-century king of the Ostrogoths who eventually became the ruler of Italy. By Theodoric's time the Ostrogoths were partially Romanized and his name was regularly recorded as Theodoricus. The Gothic original may have been Þiudreiks.
name: THEODORIC

meaning: Latinized form of the Greek name Θεοδοσιος (Theodosios) which meant "giving to god", derived from θεος (theos) "god" and δοσις (dosis) "giving". Saint Theodosius of Palestine was a monk who founded a monastery near Bethlehem in the 5th century. This also was the name of emperors of the Eastern Roman and Byzantine Empires.
name: THEODOSIUS

meaning: Latinized form of the Greek name Θεοδοτος (Theodotos) which meant "given to god" from θεος (theos) "god" and δοτος (dotos) "given". This name belonged to several early saints and martyrs.
name: THEODOTUS

meaning: Latinized form of the Greek name Θεοδουλος (Theodoulos) which meant "slave of god", derived from θεος (theos) "god" and δουλος (doulos) "slave". This name was borne by several early saints.
name: THEODULUS

meaning: Meaning unknown. In Polynesian mythology he was the god of the sea, the son of Rangi and Papa. He separated his parents' embrace, creating the earth and the sky.
name: TANGAROA

meaning: Invented name, probably modeled on TAMIKA and influenced by TANYA.
name: TANIKA
TANJA
origin: [German, Finnish, Serbian, Croatian, Slovene, Macedonian, Danish, Swedish, Norwegian]

meaning: From the name of the flower, which is derived via Old French from Late Latin tanacita.
name: TANSY

meaning: Meaning unknown. Tapio was the Finnish god of forests, animals, and hunting.
name: TAPIO

meaning: Anglicized form of the Irish place name Teamhair, which possibly means "elevated place" in Gaelic. This was the name of the sacred hill near Dublin where the Irish high kings resided. It was popularized as a given name by the novel 'Gone with the Wind' (1936) and the subsequent movie adaptation (1939), in which it is the name of the O'Hara plantation.
name: TARA  (1)

meaning: Derived from Celtic taran meaning "thunder", cognate with Þórr (see THOR). This was the name of the Gaulish thunder god, who was often identified with the Roman god Jupiter.
name: TARANIS

meaning: Bosnian form of TARIQ. It is also a variant transcription of the Arabic name.
name: TARIK

meaning: Means "he who knocks at the door" in Arabic. This is the Arabic name of the morning star. Tariq ibn Ziyad was the Islamic general who conquered Spain for the Umayyad Caliphate in the 8th century.
name: TARIQ

meaning: From the Roman name Tarquinius which is of unknown meaning, possibly Etruscan in origin. This was the name of two early kings of Rome.
name: TARQUIN

meaning: Means "legend, myth" in Finnish. It is also used as a diminutive of TARJA.
name: TARU

meaning: Means "a spring in paradise" in Arabic.
name: TASNIM
TATJANA
origin: [Serbian, Croatian, Slovene, Macedonian, German, Latvian, Lithuanian, Finnish]

meaning: Means "lion" in Tswana and Sotho. Tau was the name of the last ruler of the Rolong in South Africa (18th century).
name: TAU

meaning: Means "good fortune", derived from Arabic وفق (wafiqa) "to be successful".
name: TAWFIQ

meaning: From an English surname which originally denoted someone who was a tailor, from Norman French tailleur, ultimately from Latin taliare "to cut". Its modern use as a feminine name may have been influenced by British author Taylor Caldwell (1900-1985).
name: TAYLOR

meaning: Short form of DOROTHEA or THEODORA.
name: TEA

meaning: Means "panther passing across" in Shawnee. This was the name of a Shawnee leader who, with his brother Tenskwatawa, resisted European expansion in the early 19th century.
name: TECUMSEH

meaning: Possibly derived from Welsh teg "fair", or possibly from the Roman name TACITUS. This is the Welsh name of a lake in Wales, called Bala Lake in English. It also occurs in medieval Welsh legends as the husband of Ceridwen.
name: TEGID

meaning: Georgian form of TAHMURAS. This was the name of several kings who ruled over kingdoms located in what is now modern Georgia.
name: TEIMURAZ

meaning: Georgian and Hungarian form of THEKLA.
name: TEKLA

meaning: Short form of TERENCE or TERRY  (1).
name: TEL

meaning: Meaning unknown. Tellervo was a Finnish forest goddess. She is variously described as either the wife or daughter of Tapio.
name: TELLERVO

meaning: Derived from a misdivision of Spanish Santelmo meaning "saint ELMO". This name is given in honour of Pedro González Telmo, a 13th-century Spanish priest.
name: TELMO

meaning: Means "enough to give thanks" in Yoruba.
name: TEMITOPE

meaning: From the English word meaning "moderation" or "restraint". This was one of the virtue names adopted by the Puritans in the 17th century.
name: TEMPERANCE

meaning: From a surname which originally belonged to a person who was associated with the Knights Templar, a medieval religious military order.
name: TEMPLE

meaning: Means "of iron" in Mongolian, derived ultimately from the Turkic word temür "iron". This was the original name of the Mongolian leader better known by the title Genghis Khan. Born in the 12th century, he managed to unite the tribes of Mongolia and then conquer huge areas of Asia and Eastern Europe.
name: TEMUJIN

meaning: Means "open door" in Shawnee. This was the name of a Shawnee prophet. With his brother Tecumseh he led his people in resistance against European expansion in the early 19th century.
name: TENSKWATAWA

meaning: Short form of TEODORO and other names that begin with Teo.
name: TEO
TEODOR
origin: [Swedish, Norwegian, Danish, Romanian, Bulgarian, Slovak, Czech, Polish, Serbian, Croatian, Slovene, Macedonian]

name: TEODORA
origin: [Italian, Spanish, Portuguese, Swedish, Romanian, Polish, Bulgarian, Macedonian, Serbian]

meaning: Italian and Polish feminine form of THEOPHILUS.
name: TEOFILA

meaning: From the Roman family name Terentius which is of unknown meaning. Famous bearers include Publius Terentius Afer, a Roman playwright, and Marcus Terentius Varro, a Roman scholar. It was also borne by several early saints. The name was used in Ireland as an Anglicized form of TOIRDHEALBHACH, but it was not in use as an English name until the late 19th century.
name: TERENCE

meaning: Basque and Scandinavian form of TERESA.
name: TERESE

meaning: Hungarian and Slovak form of THERESA.
name: TERÉZIA

meaning: Slovene and Croatian form of THERESA.
name: TEREZIJA

meaning: Short form of Terhenetär, which was derived from Finnish terhen "mist". In the Finnish epic the 'Kalevala' Terhenetär is a sprite associated with mist and forests.
name: TERHI

meaning: Either a strictly feminine form of TERRY  (1) or a diminutive of THERESA.
name: TERI

meaning: Variant of TARA  (1), perhaps influenced by the Latin word terra meaning "land, earth".
name: TERRA

meaning: From an English surname which was probably derived from the Norman French nickname tirel "to pull", referring to a stubborn person. It may sometimes be given in honour of civil rights activist Mary Church Terrell (1863-1954).
name: TERRELL

meaning: Either a strictly feminine form of TERRY  (1) or a diminutive of THERESA.
name: TERRI

meaning: From an English surname which was derived from the medieval name Thierry, a Norman French form of THEODORIC.
name: TERRY  (1)

meaning: This was both a Roman praenomen and a cognomen which meant "third" in Latin.
name: TERTIUS

meaning: Diminutive of THERESA. This is the name of the main character in Thomas Hardy's novel 'Tess of the D'Ubervilles' (1891).
name: TESS

meaning: Derived from Greek τηθη (tethe) meaning "grandmother". In Greek mythology this was the name of a Titan associated with the sea. She was the wife of Oceanus.
name: TETHYS

meaning: Means "smoking mirror" in Nahuatl. In Aztec and other Mesoamerican mythology he was one of the chief gods, associated with the night sky, winds, war, and the north. Like his rival Quetzalcoatl, he was a creator god.
name: TEZCATLIPOCA

meaning: From the Greek Θαλεια (Thaleia), derived from θαλλω (thallo) meaning "to blossom". In Greek mythology she was one of the nine Muses, the muse of comedy and pastoral poetry. This was also the name of one of the three Graces or Χαριτες (Charites).
name: THALIA

meaning: Form of TAMAR used in the Greek and Latin Old Testament.
name: THAMAR

meaning: Means "death" in Greek. This was the name of the Greek god of death who resided with Hades in the underworld.
name: THANATOS

meaning: From Sino-Vietnamese 青 (thanh) meaning "blue, green, young" or 聲 (thanh) meaning "sound, voice, tone".
name: THANH

meaning: From the English word thankful. This was one of the many virtue names used by the Puritans in the 17th century.
name: THANKFUL

meaning: Short form of DOROTHEA or THEODORA.
name: THEA

meaning: Short form of THEODORA. A famous bearer was actress Theda Bara (1885-1955), who was born Theodosia Goodman.
name: THEDA

meaning: Possibly derived from Greek θεα (thea) meaning "goddess". In Greek myth this was the name of a Titan goddess of sight, glittering and glory. She was the wife of Hyperion and the mother of the sun god Helios, the moon goddess Selene, and the dawn goddess Eos.
name: THEIA

meaning: Meaning unknown. It was a rare name when British author Marie Corelli used it for the Norwegian heroine of her novel 'Thelma' (1887). The name became popular around the end of the 19th century after the novel was published. It is sometimes claimed to derive from Greek θελημα (thelema) meaning "will", though this seems unlikely.
name: THELMA

meaning: Means "law of nature, divine law, that which is laid down" in Greek. In Greek mythology this was the name of a Titan who presided over custom and natural law. She was often depicted blindfolded and holding a pair of scales. By Zeus she was the mother of many deities, including the three Μοιραι (Moirai) and the three ‘Ωραι (Horai).
name: THEMIS

meaning: Derived from the Germanic elements theud "people" and bald "bold". The Normans brought the name to England, where it joined an existing Old English cognate. The medieval forms Tibald and Tebald were commonly Latinized as Theobaldus. It was rare by the 20th century.
name: THEOBALD

meaning: Germanic name composed of the elements theud "people" and wart "watcher".
name: THEODOARD

meaning: German form of THEODORE, as well as a Scandinavian, Czech and Romanian variant of TEODOR. A famous bearer was American children's book creator Theodor Seuss Geisel (1904-1991), better known as Dr. Seuss.
name: THEODOR

meaning: Feminine form of THEODORE. This name was common in the Byzantine Empire, being borne by several empresses including the influential wife of Justinian in the 6th century.
name: THEODORA

meaning: From the Greek name Θεοδωρος (Theodoros), which meant "gift of god" from Greek θεος (theos) "god" and δωρον (doron) "gift". This was the name of several saints, including Theodore of Amasea, a 4th-century Greek soldier; Theodore of Tarsus, a 7th-century archbishop of Canterbury; and Theodore the Studite, a 9th-century Byzantine monk. It was also borne by two popes.... [more]
name: THEODORE

meaning: Latinized form of the Greek name Theodoros (see THEODORE).
name: THEODORUS

meaning: Means "manifestation of God" from Greek θεος (theos) "god" and φανης (phanes) "appearing". This name was borne by a few saints, including an 8th-century chronicler from Constantinople and a 19th-century Russian Orthodox saint, Theophanes the Recluse, who is Феофан (Feofan) in Russian. Another famous bearer was a 14th-century Byzantine icon painter active in Moscow.
name: THEOPHANES

meaning: Means "watched by god" from Greek θεος (theos) "god" and φυλακτεος (phylakteos) "to be watched". Saint Theophylaktos was a 9th-century bishop of Nicomedia who was banished to Caria.
name: THEOPHYLAKTOS

meaning: Latinized form of the Greek name Θεοτιμος (Theotimos), derived from the elemenets θεος (theos) "god" and τιμαω (timao) "to honour". Saint Theotimus was a 4th-century bishop of Tomi in Scythia.
name: THEOTIMUS

meaning: From the Spanish and Portuguese name Teresa. It was first recorded as Therasia, being borne by the Spanish wife of Saint Paulinus of Nola in the 4th century. The meaning is uncertain, but it could be derived from Greek θερος (theros) "summer", from Greek θεριζω (therizo) "to harvest", or from the name of the Greek island of Therasia (the western island of Santorini).... [more]
name: THERESA

meaning: German and Scandinavian variant of THERESA.
name: THERESE

meaning: Derived from Greek θηραω (therao) meaning "to hunt".
name: THERON

meaning: Possibly derived from Greek τιθημι (tithemi) meaning "to set, to place". Theseus was a heroic king of Athens in Greek mythology. He was the son of Aethra, either by Aegeus or by the god Poseidon. According to legend, every seven years the Cretan king Minos demanded that Athens supply Crete with seven boys and seven girls to be devoured by the Minotaur, a half-bull creature that was the son of Minos's wife Pasiphaë. Theseus volunteered to go in place of one of these youths in order to slay the Minotaur in the Labyrinth where it lived. He succeeded with the help of Minos's daughter Ariadne, who provided him with a sword and a roll of string so he could find his way out of the maze.
name: THESEUS

meaning: From Sino-Vietnamese 詩 (thi) meaning "poetry, poem, verse".
name: THI

meaning: Greek form of the Aramaic name תָּאוֹמָא (Ta'oma') which meant "twin". In the New Testament this is the name of an apostle. When he heard that Jesus had risen from the dead he initially doubted the story, until Jesus appeared before him and he examined his wounds himself. According to tradition he was martyred in India. Due to his renown, the name came into general use in the Christian world.... [more]
name: THOMAS
origin: [English, French, German, Dutch, Swedish, Norwegian, Danish, Greek, Biblical, Biblical Latin, Biblical Greek]

meaning: From the Old Norse Þórr meaning "thunder", ultimately from the early Germanic *Þunraz. Thor was the Norse god of strength, thunder, war and storms, the son of Odin. He was armed with a hammer called Mjolnir, and wore an enchanted belt that doubled his strength.
name: THOR

meaning: From a Scottish and English surname which was derived from the Norse name Þórbjörn (see TORBJÖRN).
name: THORBURN

meaning: Derived from the Old Norse elements Þórr (see THOR) and friðr "peace".
name: ÞÓRFREÐR

meaning: Means "Thor's warrior" from the name of the Norse god Þórr (see THOR) combined with Old Norse vér "warrior, fighter".
name: ÞÓRIR

meaning: From a surname which was derived from a place name meaning "thorn clearing" in Old English.
name: THORLEY

meaning: From a surname which was derived from a place name meaning "thorn town" in Old English.
name: THORNTON

meaning: Original Old Norse form of THOR.
name: ÞÓRR

meaning: Derived from the name of the Norse god Þórr (see THOR) combined with veig "strength".
name: ÞÓRVEIG

meaning: Greek form of Egyptian Djhwty (reconstructed as Djehuti), which is of uncertain meaning. In Egyptian mythology Thoth was the god of the moon, science, magic, speech and writing. He was often depicted as a man with the head of an ibis.
name: THOTH

meaning: From a Roman name which meant "of Thracia". Thracia was a region in southeast Europe, now divided between Greece and Turkey.
name: THRACIUS

meaning: From the Greek name Θουκυδιδης (Thoukydides), derived from θεος (theos) "god" (genitive θεου) and κυδος (kydos) "glory" with the patronymic suffix ιδης (ides). This was the name of a 5th-century BC Athenian historian.
name: THUCYDIDES

meaning: Means "the Pleiades" in Arabic. The Pleiades are a group of seven stars in the constellation Taurus.
name: THURAYYA

meaning: From Τουθμωσις (Touthmosis), the Greek form of Egyptian Djhwty-ms meaning "born of Thoth", itself composed of the name of the Egyptian god THOTH combined with mesu "be born". Thutmose was the name of four Egyptian pharaohs of the New Kingdom, including Thutmose III who conquered Syria and Nubia.
name: THUTMOSE

meaning: Portuguese form of JAMES, derived from SANTIAGO.
name: TIAGO

meaning: Short form of TATIANA or CHRISTIANA.
name: TIANA

meaning: From the English word for a semicircle crown, ultimately of Greek origin.
name: TIARA

meaning: Hungarian, Czech and Slovak form of Tiburtius (see TIBURCIO).
name: TIBOR

meaning: Spanish and Portuguese form of the Roman cognomen Tiburtius which meant "of Tibur". Tibur (now called Tivoli) was a resort town near Rome. Saint Tiburtius was a 3rd-century martyr from Rome.
name: TIBURCIO

meaning: Medieval form of THEOPHANIA. This name was traditionally given to girls born on the Epiphany (January 6), the festival commemorating the visit of the Magi to the infant Jesus. The name died out after the Middle Ages, but it was revived by the movie 'Breakfast at Tiffany's' (1961), the title of which refers to the Tiffany's jewelry store in New York.
name: TIFFANY

meaning: From the name of the large striped cat, derived (via Old French and Latin) from Greek τιγρις (tigris), ultimately of Iranian origin. A famous bearer is American golfer Tiger Woods (1975-).
name: TIGER

meaning: Derived from Irish Gaelic tigern meaning "lord". This was the name of an Irish saint of the 6th century. In his youth he was kidnapped by Welsh pirates and brought to Wales, but he escaped to Scotland. Eventually he returned to Ireland where he was a bishop of Clogher.
name: TIGHEARNACH

meaning: Short form of Slavic names beginning with the element tikhu "quiet".
name: TIHANA

meaning: Finnish and Estonian form of TITUS.
name: TIITUS

meaning: From Tielo, a Medieval Low German diminutive of names that began with Diet (for example DIETRICH), originally from Germanic theud meaning "people".
name: TILL

meaning: From Tielo, a Low German diminutive of names that began with Diet (for example DIETRICH), from the Germanic element theud meaning "people". Saint Tillo was a 7th-century man of Saxony who was kidnapped and brought to the Low Countries by raiders. After his release he became a Benedictine monk and did missionary work in France.
name: TILO

meaning: Latin, BiblicalLatinized form of the Greek name Τιμαιος (Timaios), derived from τιμαω (timao) "to honour". This is the name of one of Plato's dialogues, featuring Timaeus and Socrates. Timaeus is also the name of a person mentioned briefly in the New Testament (Mark 10:46).
name: TIMAEUS

meaning: Created by the Hungarian author Mór Jókai for a character in his novel 'The Golden Man' (1873). The name is apparently based on the Greek word ευθυμια (euthymia) meaning "good spirits, cheerfulness".
name: TÍMEA

meaning: From Thiemo, an old short form of Thietmar (see DIETMAR).
name: TIMO  (2)

meaning: Derived from Greek τιμαω (timao) meaning "to honour, to esteem". It appears briefly in the New Testament. This is also the name of the main character in Shakespeare's tragedy 'Timon of Athens' (1607).
name: TIMON
origin: [Ancient Greek, Biblical, Biblical Greek, Biblical Latin, Dutch]

meaning: Slovene, Macedonian and Slovak form of TIMOTHY.
name: TIMOTEJ

meaning: English form of the Greek name Τιμοθεος (Timotheos) meaning "honouring God", derived from τιμαω (timao) "to honour" and θεος (theos) "god". Saint Timothy was a companion of Paul on his missionary journeys and was the recipient of two of Paul's epistles that appear in the New Testament. He was of both Jewish and Greek ancestry. According to tradition, he was martyred at Ephesus after protesting the worship of Artemis. As an English name, Timothy was not used until after the Protestant Reformation.
name: TIMOTHY

meaning: Croatian short form of MARTIN, AUGUSTIN, and other names ending in tin.
name: TIN

meaning: Means "God is with us" in Shona.
name: TINASHE

meaning: Slovene diminutive of MARTIN or VALENTIN.
name: TINE  (2)

meaning: Means "nightingale" in Sindarin. In the 'Silmarillion' (1977) by J. R. R. Tolkien, Tinuviel was the daughter of Thingol the elf king and the beloved of Beren, who with her help retrieved one of the Silmarils from the iron crown of Morgoth.
name: TINUVIEL

meaning: Possibly means "desire" in Hebrew. Tiras is a grandson of Noah in the Old Testament.
name: TIRAS

meaning: Means "sacred water, place of pilgrimage" in Indonesian, ultimately from Sanskrit तीर्थ (tirtha).
name: TIRTA

meaning: Short form of LETITIA or LATISHA.
name: TISHA

meaning: Italian, Spanish and Portuguese form of TITUS.
name: TITO

meaning: Italian form of the Roman cognomen Titianus, which was derived from the Roman praenomen TITUS. A famous bearer was the Venetian Renaissance painter Tiziano Vecellio (1488-1576), known in English as Titian.
name: TIZIANO

meaning: Greek form of TOBIAH. This is the name of the hero of the apocryphal Book of Tobit, which appears in many English versions of the Old Testament. It relates how Tobit's son Tobias, with the help of the angel Raphael, is able to drive away a demon who has plagued Sarah, who subsequently becomes his wife. This story was popular in the Middle Ages, and the name came into occasional use in parts of Europe at that time. In England it became common after the Protestant Reformation.
name: TOBIAS
origin: [Biblical, German, Swedish, Norwegian, Danish, English, Biblical Latin, Biblical Greek]

meaning: From an English surname which was itself derived from the given name TOBIAS.
name: TOBIN

meaning: Bulgarian and Macedonian feminine form of THEODORE.
name: TODORKA

meaning: Short form of ÞÓRFREÐR or ÞÓRFASTR.
name: TÓFI

meaning: Means "the end" from Hebrew תּוֹם (tom). It can also be a variant transcription of TAM  (2).
name: TOM  (2)

meaning: Czech and Slovak form of THOMAS.
name: TOMÁŠ

meaning: Swedish, Norwegian and Lithuanian form of THOMAS.
name: TOMAS

meaning: Probably derived from the Slavic element tomiti meaning "torture" combined with slava meaning "glory". This was the name of the first king of Croatia (10th century).
name: TOMISLAV

meaning: Diminutive of THOMAS, sometimes used as a feminine form.
name: TOMMIE

meaning: Either a variant of TOMA  (2) or a diminutive of TOMISLAV.
name: TOMO

meaning: From Japanese 朋 (tomo) meaning "friend" and 美 (mi) meaning "beautiful". Other kanji combinations can also form this name.
name: TOMOMI

meaning: Latinized form of the Greek name Θεοφιλος (Theophilos) which meant "friend of god", derived from θεος (theos) "god" and φιλος (philos) "friend". In the New Testament the evangelist Luke addresses his gospel and the Book of Acts to a man named Theophilus.
name: THEOPHILUS

meaning: French form of THERESA. It was borne by the French nun Saint Thérèse de Lisieux (1873-1897), who is regarded as a Doctor of the Church.
name: THÉRÈSE

meaning: German, Dutch and Swedish form of THERESA.
name: THERESIA

meaning: Form of TIRZAH used in the Greek and Latin Old Testament.
name: THERSA

meaning: From Sino-Vietnamese 氏 (thị) meaning "clan, family, maiden name". This is a very common middle name for Vietnamese girls.
name: THỊ

meaning: Either a feminine form of Þórr (see THOR) or else a short form of the various Old Norse names beginning with the element Þór. In Norse myth Thora was the wife of the Danish king Ragnar Lodbrok.
name: ÞÓRA

meaning: Old Norse name derived from the name of the Norse god Þórr (see THOR) combined with arn "eagle".
name: ÞÓRARINN

meaning: Old Norse name which meant "Thor's protection" from the name of the Norse god Þórr (see THOR) combined with björg "help, save, rescue".
name: ÞÓRBJÖRG

meaning: Means "Thor's goddess" from the name of the Norse god Þórr (see THOR) combined with Old Norse dís "goddess".
name: ÞÓRDÍS

meaning: Derived from the Old Norse elements Þórr (see THOR) and fastr "firm".
name: ÞÓRFASTR

meaning: Derived from the Old Norse elements Þórr (see THOR) and fríðr "beautiful".
name: ÞÓRFRÍÐR

meaning: Old Norse name meaning "Thor's shaft" from the name of the Norse god Þórr (see THOR) combined with gísl "shaft, arrow".
name: ÞÓRGÍSL

meaning: Derived from the name of the Norse god Þórr (see THOR) combined with ví "holy".
name: ÞÓRVÍ

meaning: From Sino-Vietnamese 純 (thuần) meaning "pure, clean, simple".
name: THUẦN

meaning: Means "be quiet, be comforted" in Zulu.
name: THULANI

meaning: From an English surname which was derived from the Norse name Þórsteinn (see TORSTEN).
name: THURSTAN

meaning: From Sino-Vietnamese 垂 (thùy) meaning "let down, suspend, hang".
name: THÙY

meaning: Short form of names ending with tia. It has been suggested that its use since the 1950s is the result of the brand name for the coffee liqueur Tia Maria. In the brand name, Tia is not a given name; rather, it means "aunt" in Spanish or Portuguese.
name: TIA

meaning: Means "sea" in Akkadian. In Babylonian myth Tiamat was the personification of the sea, appearing in the form of a huge dragon. By Apsu she gave birth to the first of the gods. Later, the god Marduk (her great-grandson) defeated her, cut her in half, and used the pieces of her body to make the earth and the sky.
name: TIAMAT

meaning: Roman praenomen, or given name, meaning "of the Tiber" in Latin. The Tiber is the river that runs through Rome. Tiberius was the second Roman emperor, the stepson of emperor Augustus.
name: TIBERIUS

meaning: Germanic name derived from the elements theud "people" and man "man".
name: TIEDEMANN

meaning: From Sino-Vietnamese 仙 (tiên) meaning "immortal, transcendent, celestial being, fairy".
name: TIÊN

meaning: Anglicized form of TIGHEARNACH. In part, it is from a surname derived from the given name.
name: TIERNEY

meaning: Diminutive of MATTHIJS as well as Dutch names beginning with the Germanic element theud meaning "people".
name: TIES

meaning: Means "little lord" from Irish Gaelic tigern "lord" combined with a diminutive suffix. This was the name of a 12th-century king of Breifne in Ireland.
name: TIGHEARNÁN

meaning: Derived from the Slavic elements tikhu "quiet" and miru "peace, world".
name: TIHOMIR

meaning: Short form of MARTIJN or AUGUSTIJN.
name: TIJN

meaning: Dutch and Limburgish short form of MATHILDE.
name: TIL

meaning: Short form of TIMOTHY. It was borne by the fictional character Tiny Tim, the ill son of Bob Cratchit in Charles Dickens' novel 'A Christmas Carol' (1843).
name: TIM
origin: [English, German, Dutch, Slovene, Swedish, Norwegian, Danish]

meaning: Finnish, German and Dutch short form of Timotheus (see TIMOTHY).
name: TIMO  (1)

meaning: Bulgarian and Romanian form of TIMOTHY.
name: TIMOTEI

meaning: Italian, Spanish and Portuguese form of TIMOTHY.
name: TIMOTEO

meaning: From the Turkic name Temür meaning "iron". Timur, also known as Tamerlane (from Persian تیمور  لنگ (Timur e Lang) meaning "Timur the lame"), was a 14th-century Turkic leader who conquered large areas of Western Asia.
name: TIMUR

meaning: Short form of CHRISTINA, MARTINA, and other names ending in tina. In addition to these names, it is also used in Dutch as a diminutive of CATHARINA and in Croatian as a diminutive of KATARINA.
name: TINA

meaning: Possibly related to Georgian სინათლე (sinatle) "light". The name was devised by the Georgian poet Shota Rustaveli for his 12th-century epic poem 'The Knight in the Panther's Skin', in which Tinatin is the ruler of Arabia and the lover of Avtandil.
name: TINATIN

meaning: Slovene diminutive of MARTIN or VALENTIN.
name: TINEK

meaning: Short form of VALENTINO, MARTINO, and other names ending in tino.
name: TINO

meaning: From the Hebrew name תִּרְצָה (Tirtzah) meaning "favourable". Tirzah is the name of one of the daughters of Zelophehad in the Old Testament. It also occurs in the Old Testament as a place name, the early residence of the kings of the northern kingdom.
name: TIRZAH

meaning: Means "avenging murder" in Greek, derived from τισις (tisis) "vengeance" and φονη (phone) "murder". This was the name of one of the Furies or Ερινυες (Erinyes) in Greek mythology. She killed Cithaeron with the bite of one of the snakes on her head.
name: TISIPHONE

meaning: Perhaps based on Latin Titanius meaning "of the Titans". This name was (first?) used by Shakespeare in his comedy 'A Midsummer Night's Dream' (1595) where it is the name of queen of the fairies. This is also a moon of Uranus, named after the Shakespearian character.
name: TITANIA

meaning: Form of TITUS used in the Greek New Testament.
name: TITOS

meaning: Diminutive of LETITIA. This is now a slang word for the female breast, and the name has subsequently dropped out of common use.
name: TITTY

meaning: Roman praenomen, or given name, which is of unknown meaning, possibly related to Latin titulus "title of honour". It is more likely of Oscan origin, since it was borne by the legendary Sabine king Titus Tatius.... [more]
name: TITUS

meaning: From the name of a picturesque Italian town, used as a summer resort by the ancient Romans.
name: TIVOLI

meaning: Means "tulip" in Welsh. This is a modern Welsh name.
name: TIWLIP

meaning: Means "of the earth" in Nahuatl. He was the Aztec god of rain and fertility, the husband of Chalchiuhticue.
name: TLALOC

meaning: From the Hebrew name טוֹבִיָּה (Toviyyah) which meant "YAHWEH is good". This was the name of an Ammonite in the Book of Nehemiah in the Old Testament.
name: TOBIAH

meaning: From Greek Τωβιθ (Tobith), from the Hebrew name טוֹבִיה (Tovih) meaning "my good". The apocryphal Book of Tobit, which is canonical in many Christian traditions but not in Judaism, tells the story of Tobit's son Tobias. He is sent by his father to collect money in Media, aided by the angel Raphael in the guise of a man. At the end of the story Tobit's blindness is cured.
name: TOBIT

meaning: Medieval form of TOBIAS. It was sometimes used as a feminine name in the 1930s and 40s due to the influence of American actress Toby Wing (1915-2001).
name: TOBY

meaning: From a surname meaning "fox", derived from Middle English todde.
name: TODD

meaning: Bulgarian, Serbian and Macedonian form of THEODORE.
name: TODOR

meaning: From the Old Norse name Þórleikr, which meant "Thor's play" from the name of the Norse god Þórr (see THOR) combined with leikr "play, game (involving weapons)".
name: TOLLAK

meaning: Short form of THOMAS. Tom Sawyer was the main character in several of Mark Twain's novels, first appearing in 'The Adventures of Tom Sawyer' (1876). Other famous bearers include American actors Tom Hanks (1956-) and Tom Cruise (1962-).
name: TOM  (1)

meaning: Spanish, Portuguese and Irish form of THOMAS.
name: TOMÁS

meaning: Finnish, Hungarian and Welsh diminutive of THOMAS.
name: TOMI

meaning: From Japanese 富 (tomi) meaning "wealth, abundance" and 子 (ko) meaning "child". Other combinations of kanji can also form this name.
name: TOMIKO

meaning: From Japanese 智 (tomo) meaning "wisdom, intellect" or 朋 (tomo) meaning "friend" combined with 子 (ko) meaning "child". This name can be formed of other kanji characters as well.
name: TOMOKO

meaning: Short form of ANTTONI, ANTUN, and other related names.
name: TONI  (1)

meaning: Portuguese diminutive of ANTÓNIO or ANTÔNIO.
name: TONINHO

meaning: Short form of ANTONIA. Its use was probably positively influenced by the name TANYA.
name: TONYA

meaning: Modern Scandinavian form of Þórr (see THOR). It was not used as a personal name until the 18th century. It is sometimes used as a short form of names of Old Norse origin that begin with the element Tor, which is also from Þórr.
name: TOR

meaning: From the Old Norse name Þórbjörn, which meant "Thor's bear" from the name of the Norse god Þórr (see THOR) combined with björn "bear".
name: TORBJÖRN

meaning: From the Old Norse name Þórgnýr meaning "Thor's noise" from the name of the Norse god Þórr (see THOR) combined with gnýr "noise, grumble, murmur".
name: TORGNY

meaning: Spanish form of the Roman cognomen Turibius, of unknown meaning. Saint Toribio was a 16th-century archbishop of Lima.
name: TORIBIO

meaning: From the Old Norse name Þórketill meaning "Thor's cauldron" from the name of the Norse god Þórr (see THOR) combined with ketill "cauldron".
name: TORKEL

meaning: From the Old Norse name Þórmóðr, which meant "Thor's mind" from the name of the Norse god Þórr (see THOR) combined with móðr "mind, mood".
name: TORMOD

meaning: From the Old Norse name Þórný which was derived from the name of the Norse god Þórr (see THOR) combined with ný "new".
name: TORNY

meaning: Meaning unknown, possibly a diminutive of SALVATORE.
name: TORY  (1)

meaning: Variant transcription of TOSHE. This is the usual Romanized spelling of the name of the Macedonian pop star Toše Proeski (1981-2007).
name: TOŠE

meaning: Means "all saints" in French. This is the name of a Christian festival celebrated on November 1.
name: TOUSSAINT

meaning: From an English surname which was taken from a Norman French place name meaning "domain belonging to THRACIUS". Charles Dickens used it for a male character in his novel 'The Pickwick Papers' (1837). It was later popularized as a feminine name by the main character Tracy Lord in the movie 'The Philadelphia Story' (1940). This name is also sometimes used as a diminutive of THERESA.
name: TRACY

meaning: Means "very much like iron", derived from Welsh tra "very, over" and haearn "iron".
name: TRAHAEARN

meaning: From a surname meaning "wagoner" in Old English.
name: TRANTER

meaning: Derived from German trau "trust" and Gott "God". This name was created in the 17th century.
name: TRAUGOTT

meaning: From the English surname Travis (a variant of TRAVERS). It was used in America in honour of William Travis (1809-1836), the commander of the Texan forces at the Battle of the Alamo.
name: TRAVIS

meaning: Derived from Macedonian трендафил (trendafil) meaning "eglantine, sweet briar".
name: TRENDAFILKA

meaning: From the name of a New Jersey city established in the 17th century by William Trent. It means "TRENT's town".
name: TRENTON

meaning: From a surname which was originally from a place name meaning "big village" from Welsh tref "village" and mawr "large".
name: TREVOR

meaning: Means "three, third" in Indonesian, ultimately from Sanskrit त्रि (tri).
name: TRI

meaning: From the English word Trinity, given in honour of the Christian belief that God has one essence, but three distinct expressions of being: Father, Son and Holy Spirit. It has only been in use as a given name since the 20th century.
name: TRINITY

meaning: Old French form of the Pictish name Drustan, a diminutive of DRUST. The spelling was altered by association with Latin tristis "sad". Tristan is a character in medieval French tales, probably inspired by older Celtic legends, and ultimately merged into Arthurian legend. According to the story Tristan was sent to Ireland in order to fetch Isolde, who was to be the bride of King Mark of Cornwall. On the way back, Tristan and Isolde accidentally drink a potion which makes them fall in love. Their tragic story was very popular in the Middle Ages, and the name has occasionally been used since that time.
name: TRISTAN

meaning: Variant of TRISTAN, sometimes used as a feminine form.
name: TRISTEN

meaning: From a surname that originally denoted a person from the city of Troyes in France. This was also the name of the ancient city that was besieged by the Greeks in Homer's 'Iliad'.
name: TROY

meaning: From a surname which was a variant of TRUMAN.
name: TRUEMAN

meaning: From a surname which meant "trusty man" in Middle English. A famous bearer of the surname was American president Harry S. Truman (1884-1972). It was also borne by American writer Truman Capote (1924-1984).
name: TRUMAN

meaning: Old Norse and Icelandic form of TRYGVE.
name: TRYGGVI

meaning: Derived from Greek τρυφη (tryphe) meaning "softness, delicacy". Saint Tryphon, a gooseherder from Syria, was martyred in the 3rd century.
name: TRYPHON

meaning: Means "long life" in Tibetan, from ཚེ (tshe) meaning "life" and རིང (ring) meaning "long".
name: TSHERING

meaning: Derived from Georgian ცის (tsis) meaning "of the sky", the genitive case of ცა (tsa) "sky, heaven".
name: TSISIA

meaning: From Japanese 椿 (tsubaki) meaning "camellia flower", as well as other combinations of kanji which are pronounced the same way.
name: TSUBAKI

meaning: From Japanese 翼 (tsubasa) meaning "wing", as well as other kanji or kanji combinations with the same pronunciation.
name: TSUBASA

meaning: From Chinese 图 (tú) meaning "chart, map" or other characters with similar pronunciations.
name: TU

meaning: From Sino-Vietnamese 遵 (tuân) meaning "obey, follow, honour".
name: TUÂN

meaning: From the name of a type of tree that is believed to grow in heaven in Islamic tradition. It means "blessedness" in Arabic.
name: TUBA

meaning: Welsh form of the old Celtic name Teutorigos, meaning "ruler of the people" (cognate with THEODORIC). As a surname it was borne by five monarchs of England beginning with Henry VII in the 15th century.
name: TUDOR  (1)

meaning: Italian form of the Roman family name Tullius, which is of unknown meaning. A famous bearer was Marcus Tullius Cicero, a Roman orator and author.
name: TULLIO

meaning: Form of Tullius (see TULLIO) used to refer to the Roman orator Marcus Tullius Cicero.
name: TULLY

meaning: Derived from Hungarian tündér meaning "fairy". The Hungarian poet Mihály Vörösmarty created this name in the 19th century.
name: TÜNDE

meaning: Means "strength vigour" in Sindarin. In the 'Silmarillion' (1977) by J. R. R. Tolkien, Tuor was the mortal man who came to the hidden city of Gondolin to warn of its imminent doom. When Gondolin was attacked and destroyed he escaped with his wife Idril and son Eärendil, and sailed into the west.
name: TUOR

meaning: Means "victory mood" in Sindarin. In the 'Silmarillion' (1977) by J. R. R. Tolkien, Turin was a cursed hero, the slayer of the dragon Glaurung. He was also called Turambar, Mormegil, and other names. This is also the Anglicized name of the city of Torino in Italy.
name: TURIN

meaning: Dutch and Limburgish short form of ARTHUR.
name: TUUR

meaning: Swedish and Norwegian variant of TOVE.
name: TUVA

meaning: From Sino-Vietnamese 線 (tuyến) meaning "thread, line, ray".
name: TUYẾN

meaning: Medieval form of THEOBALD. This is the name of a cousin of Juliet killed by Romeo in Shakespeare's drama 'Romeo and Juliet' (1596).
name: TYBALT

meaning: From an English surname meaning "tiler of roofs". The surname was borne by American president John Tyler (1790-1862).
name: TYLER

meaning: From the Old Norse name Þýri, a variant of the Norse names ÞÓRVÍ or ÞÓRVEIG.
name: TYRA

meaning: From a surname which was a variant of TERRELL.
name: TYRELL

meaning: From a surname which was a variant of TERRELL.
name: TYRRELL

meaning: Means "heavenly beauty" or "royal beauty" from Hawaiian u'i "youth, beauty" and lani "heaven, sky, royal, majesty".
name: UILANI

meaning: Italian form of HULDERIC, sometimes considered a form of ULRICH.
name: ULDERICO

meaning: Slovene and Croatian diminutive of ANTONIA.
name: TONKA

meaning: From the English word for the yellow precious stone, the birthstone of November, ultimately derived from Greek τοπαζος (topazos).
name: TOPAZ

meaning: From a nickname which is of unknown meaning, perhaps deriving from the English word top.
name: TOPSY

meaning: Danish and Norwegian form of TORBJÖRN.
name: TORBJØRN

meaning: Probably from the Old Norse name ÞÓRIR.
name: TORE  (1)

meaning: From the Old Norse name Þórgeirr, which meant "Thor's spear" from the name of the Norse god Þórr (see THOR) combined with geirr "spear".
name: TORGEIR

meaning: From the Old Norse name Þórhildr, which meant "Thor's battle" from the name of the Norse god Þórr (see THOR) combined with hildr "battle".
name: TORHILD

meaning: From the Old Norse name Þórleifr meaning "Thor's descendant" from the name of the Norse god Þórr (see THOR) combined with leifr "descendant, heir".
name: TORLEIF

meaning: Georgian form of Greek Τορνικιος (Tornikios) or Τορνικης (Tornikes), the name of a prominent Byzantine family that was of Armenian or Georgian descent. The family name may be derived from Armenian թոռնիկ (tornik), a diminutive of թոռն (torn) meaning "grandchild". Usage as a given name probably began in honour of the family, a notable member of which was a saint.
name: TORNIKE

meaning: From the Old Norse name Þórsteinn, which meant "Thor's stone" from the name of the Norse god Þórr (see THOR) combined with steinn "stone".
name: TORSTEN

meaning: From the Old Norse name Þórvaldr, which meant "Thor's ruler" from the name of the Norse god Þórr (see THOR) combined with valdr "ruler".
name: TORVALD

meaning: Modern form of the Old Norse name Tófa, a short form of ÞÓRFRÍÐR.
name: TOVE

meaning: Hebrew form of TOBIAH, also used as a feminine form.
name: TOVIA

meaning: Diminutive of VICTORIA or CUSTODIA used among Hispanic Americans.
name: TOYA

meaning: From a surname which was derived from a place name meaning "fishtrap ford" in Old English.
name: TRAFFORD

meaning: From the Roman cognomen Traianus, which is of unknown meaning. The Roman emperor Trajan (full name Marcus Ulpius Traianus) is considered among the most capable men to have led the empire. His military accomplishments include victories over Dacia and Parthia.
name: TRAJAN

meaning: Possibly means "strength" in Irish Gaelic. It is also sometimes used as an Irish form of THERESA.
name: TREASA

meaning: From the English word, ultimately from Greek θησαυρος (thesauros) "treasure, collection".
name: TREASURE

meaning: Dutch and Limburgish short form of THERESIA.
name: TREES

meaning: From a surname which originally denoted someone who lived by the River Trent in England. Trent is also a city in Italy, though the etymology is unrelated.
name: TRENT

meaning: From a surname which was derived from a Cornish place name meaning "homestead on the hill".
name: TREVELYAN

meaning: Perhaps a short form of DEMETRIA and other names ending in a similar sound.
name: TRIA

meaning: Means "trinity" in Spanish, referring to the Holy Trinity. An island in the West Indies bears this name.
name: TRINIDAD

meaning: Variant of TRISTAN, sometimes used as a feminine form.
name: TRISTIN

meaning: From the Old Norse byname Þróndr which indicated a person from Trøndelag, a region in central Norway, possibly derived from þróast meaning "to grow, to prosper".
name: TROND

meaning: Diminutive of GERTRUDE and other Germanic names ending with the element thrud "strength".
name: TRUDI

meaning: Norwegian and Swedish form of ÞÓRGÍSL.
name: TRULS

meaning: Derived from Old Norse tryggr meaning "trustworthy".
name: TRYGVE

meaning: From the Greek name Τρυφαινα (Tryphaina), derived from Greek τρυφη (tryphe) meaning "softness, delicacy". This name is mentioned briefly in the New Testament.
name: TRYPHENA

meaning: Derived from Greek τρυφη (tryphe) meaning "softness, delicacy". In the New Testament this name is mentioned briefly as belonging to a companion of Tryphena.
name: TRYPHOSA

meaning: Probably derived from Georgian ცის (tsis) meaning "of the sky", the genitive case of ცა (tsa) "sky, heaven".
name: TSISANA

meaning: Means "heavenly, celestial" in Georgian, a derivative of ცა (tsa) "sky, heaven".
name: TSIURI

meaning: From Japanese 燕 (tsubame) meaning "swallow (bird)" or other kanji which have the same pronunciation.
name: TSUBAME

meaning: From Japanese 月 (tsuki) meaning "moon" and 子 (ko) meaning "child". Other combinations of kanji are possible.
name: TSUKIKO

meaning: Derived from Bulgarian цвет (tsvet) meaning "flower, blossom".
name: TSVETAN

meaning: From Sino-Vietnamese 秀 (tú) meaning "luxuriant, beautiful, elegant, outstanding".
name: TÚ

meaning: Means "ruler of the people" in Irish Gaelic.
name: TUATHAL

meaning: From an occupational surname derived from Old English tucian meaning "one who fulls cloth".
name: TUCKER

meaning: Means "image of the life of Amon", derived from Egyptian tut "image" combined with ankh "life" combined with the name of the god Amon. This was the name of an Egyptian pharaoh of the 18th dynasty, most famous because of the treasures found in his tomb.
name: TUTANKHAMON

meaning: Means "little wind" in Finnish, derived from tuuli "wind". This was the name of a Finnish forest goddess, the daughter of Tapio.
name: TUULIKKI

meaning: Meaning unknown. Perhaps based on the English word twilight, or maybe from a Cajun pronunciation of French étoile "star". It came into use as an American given name in the late 19th century.
name: TWILA

meaning: Short form of TYLER, TYSON, TYRONE, and other names beginning with Ty.
name: TY

meaning: From the Greek name Τυχων (Tychon) meaning "hitting the mark". This was the name of a Greek saint. It was also borne by the Danish astronomer Tycho Brahe (1546-1601).
name: TYCHO

meaning: From a surname meaning "pasture" in Middle English.
name: TYE

meaning: Norse form of the name of the Germanic god Tiwaz, related to Indo-European dyeus (see ZEUS). In Norse mythology Tyr was the god of war and justice, the son of the god Odin. He carried a spear in his left hand, since his right hand was bitten off by the wolf Fenrir. At the time of the end of the world, the Ragnarok, Tyr will slay and be slain by the giant hound Garm.
name: TYR

meaning: An invented name based on the popular name syllable Tyr (from names such as TYRONE).
name: TYRESE

meaning: Probably a blend of TYRONE and TARIQ.
name: TYRIQ

meaning: From the name of a county in Northern Ireland which is derived from Irish Gaelic Tir Eoghain meaning "land of EOGHAN". This name was popularized by American actor Tyrone Power (1914-1958), who was named after his great-grandfather, an Irish actor.
name: TYRONE

meaning: From an English surname which could be derived from a nickname for a quarrelsome person, from Old French tison meaning "firebrand". Alternatively, it could be a variant of DYSON. A famous bearer of the surname was boxer Mike Tyson (1966-).
name: TYSON

meaning: Either an Irish form of the Old Norse name HUGLEIKR, or else a diminutive of UILLIAM.
name: UILLEAG

meaning: Scottish Gaelic form of the Old Norse name EYSTEINN.
name: ÙISDEAN

meaning: From Sino-Korean 宇 (u) meaning "house, eaves, universe" or 佑 (u) meaning "help, protect, bless" combined with 眞 (jin) meaning "real, genuine" or 鎭 (jin) meaning "town, market place". Other combinations of hanja characters can form this name as well.
name: U-JIN

meaning: Means "old man" in Finnish. In Finnish mythology Ukko is the god of the sky and thunder.
name: UKKO

meaning: From the Old Norse byname Úlfr meaning "wolf".
name: ULF

meaning: Scandinavian diminutive of ULRIKA or HULDA  (1), or a German diminutive of URSULA.
name: ULLA

meaning: Middle English form of the Old English name Wulfric meaning "wolf power". When it is used in modern times, it is usually as a variant of ULRICH.
name: ULRIC

meaning: From the Germanic name Odalric meaning "prosperity and power", from the element odal "heritage" combined with ric "power". It has long been confused with the Germanic name Hulderic. This was the name of two German saints. Another famous bearer was Ulrich Zwingli (1484-1531), also known as Huldrych, the leader of the Protestant Reformation in Switzerland.
name: ULRICH

meaning: Means "of Ulster" in Gaelic. Ulster is a region in the north of Ireland. This name was borne by two 7th-century Irish saints.
name: ULTÁN

meaning: Latin form of ODYSSEUS. It was borne by Ulysses S. Grant (1822-1885), the commander of the Union forces during the American Civil War, who went on to become an American president. Irish author James Joyce used it as the title of his book 'Ulysses' (1920), which loosely parallels Homer's epic the 'Odyssey'.
name: ULYSSES

meaning: Means "populous, flourishing", derived from Arabic عمر ('umr) "life". Umar was a companion and strong supporter of Muhammad who became the second caliph of the Muslims. He is considered to be one of the great founders of the Muslim state. The name was also borne by a 12th-century poet from Persia, Umar Khayyam.
name: UMAR

meaning: From Japanese 梅 (ume) meaning "plum". In Japan the plum blossom is thought to symbolize devotion. Different kanji or kanji combinations can also form this name.
name: UME

meaning: Means "hope" in Uzbek, ultimately from Persian امید (omid).
name: UMID

meaning: Means "hope" in Turkish, ultimately from Persian امید (omid).
name: ÜMİT

meaning: Variant of ÜMİT. The Turkish words umut and ümit are etymologically related synonyms.
name: UMUT

meaning: Means "God is with us" in Xhosa.
name: UNATHI

meaning: From the English word unity, which is ultimately derived from Latin unitas.
name: UNITY

meaning: Derived from Old Norse unnr "to wave, to billow" or unna "to love".
name: UNNR

meaning: From a surname which was derived from a place name meaning "upper town" in Old English. A famous bearer of this name was the American novelist Upton Sinclair (1878-1968).
name: UPTON

meaning: From the Hebrew name אוּרִיָה ('Uriyah) which meant "YAHWEH is my light". In the Old Testament this is the name of a Hittite warrior in King David's army, the first husband of Bathsheba. David desired Bathsheba so he placed Uriah in the forefront of battle so he would be killed.
name: URIAH

meaning: Means "privileged birth" from Celtic orbo "privileged" and gen "birth". In Welsh legend and Arthurian romances Urien is a king of Gore and the husband of Morgan le Fay.
name: URIEN

meaning: German form of the Latin name Ursus, which meant "bear". Saint Ursus was a 3rd-century soldier in the Theban Legion who was martyred with Saint Victor. He is the patron saint of Solothurn in Switzerland.
name: URS

meaning: Latin name which was a derivative of Ursus (see URS).
name: URSINUS

meaning: Portuguese and Spanish form of URSULA.
name: ÚRSULA

meaning: Means "little bear", derived from a diminutive form of the Latin word ursa "she-bear". Saint Ursula was a legendary virgin princess of the 4th century who was martyred by the Huns while returning from a pilgrimage. In England the saint was popular during the Middle Ages, and the name came into general use at that time.
name: URSULA
origin: [English, Swedish, Norwegian, Danish, German, Dutch, Finnish, Late Roman]

name: USHA
origin: [Hinduism, Indian, Kannada, Tamil, Telugu, Malayalam, Hindi, Marathi, Nepali]

meaning: From the Welsh name Uthyr, derived from Welsh uthr "terrible". In Arthurian legend Uther was the father of King Arthur. He appears in some early Welsh texts, but is chiefly known from the 12th-century chronicles of Geoffrey of Monmouth.
name: UTHER

meaning: Derived from Sumerian ud meaning "sun". In Sumerian mythology this was the name of the god of the sun. He was the son of the moon god Nanna and Ningal.
name: UTU

meaning: Means "my power" in Hebrew. This is the name of several minor characters in the Old Testament.
name: UZZI

meaning: Means "my power is God" in Hebrew. This is the name of several minor characters in the Old Testament.
name: UZZIEL

meaning: Flemish, Norman and Picard form of VEDASTUS.
name: VAAST

meaning: Meaning unknown. It is used as a Russian form of BADEMUS, but it may actually be derived from the Slavic name VADIMIR or else from an Old Norse source.
name: VADIM

meaning: Mythology, ArmenianFrom Avestan Verethragna meaning "breaking of defense, victory". In Armenian mythology this was the name of the heroic god of war.
name: VAHAGN

meaning: Derived from Old Persian varka-tanu meaning "wolf-bodied". This name was borne by several kings of Georgia.
name: VAKHTANG

meaning: Modern coinage from Germanic wald meaning "power, rule". It has been in use only since the 20th century.
name: VALDA

meaning: Scandinavian form of WALDEMAR. This was the name of four kings of Denmark.
name: VALDEMAR

meaning: Short form of VOLDEMĀRS and other Latvian names containing the Germanic/Baltic element wald "rule".
name: VALDIS

meaning: From the name of cities in Spain and Venezuela, both derived from Latin valentia meaning "strength, vigour".
name: VALENCIA

meaning: Spanish and Slovak form of Valentinus (see VALENTINE  (1)).
name: VALENTÍN

meaning: Slovak feminine form of Valentinus (see VALENTINE  (1)).
name: VALENTÍNA

meaning: From the Roman cognomen Valentinus which was itself from the name Valens meaning "strong, vigourous, healthy" in Latin. Saint Valentine was a 3rd-century martyr. His feast day was the same as the Roman fertility festival of Lupercalia, which resulted in the association between Valentine's day and love. As an English name, it has been used occasionally since the 12th century.
name: VALENTINE  (1)

meaning: Roman cognomen which was a derivative of the cognomen Valentinus (see VALENTINE  (1)). This name was borne by three Roman emperors.
name: VALENTINIANUS

meaning: Bulgarian and Georgian form of VALERIUS, as well as a variant transcription of the Russian name VALERIY.
name: VALERI

meaning: Feminine form of VALERIUS. This was the name of a 2nd-century Roman saint and martyr.
name: VALERIA

meaning: From the Roman cognomen Valerianus, which was itself derived from the Roman name VALERIUS. This was the name of a 3rd-century Roman emperor. Several saints also had this name, including a 2nd-century martyr of Lyons.
name: VALERIAN

meaning: French and Czech form of VALERIA.
name: VALÉRIE

meaning: Italian and Spanish form of VALERIUS.
name: VALERIO

meaning: Roman family name which was derived from Latin valere "to be strong". This was the name of several early saints.
name: VALERIUS

meaning: Russian and Ukrainian feminine form of VALERIUS.
name: VALERIYA

meaning: Derived from the Germanic elements walha "foreign" and ric "power". It has been frequently confused with the name Valère.
name: VALÉRY

meaning: Means "creeping plant" in Dravidian. In Dravidian mythology the goddess Valli was the wife of Murunga.
name: VALLI

meaning: Finnish short form of VALDEMAR or other names containing vald.
name: VALTO

meaning: Short form of names containing van, such as VANCE or IVAN.
name: VAN

meaning: Invented by author Jonathan Swift for his poem 'Cadenus and Vanessa' (1726). He arrived at it by rearranging the initial syllables of the first name and surname of Esther Vanhomrigh, his close friend. Vanessa was later used as the name of a genus of butterfly. It was a rare given name until the mid-20th century, at which point it became fairly popular.
name: VANESSA

meaning: Croatian and Serbian (masculine and feminine) form of VANYA. It is also used in Scandinavia, where it is primarily feminine.
name: VANJA

meaning: Means "golden" in Khmer, ultimately from Sanskrit.
name: VANNA  (2)

meaning: Derived from Georgian ვარდი (vardi) meaning "rose", ultimately from Persian via Armenian.
name: VARDO

meaning: Roman family name which meant "versatile" in Latin. Varius Rufus was a Roman epic poet of the 1st century BC.
name: VARIUS

meaning: From the Finnish name for a type of berry bush.
name: VARPU

meaning: Russian, Greek, Bulgarian and Macedonian form of BARBARA.
name: VARVARA

meaning: Means "brilliant" or "spring" in Sanskrit. This is the name of a Hindu personification of the spring.
name: VASANTA
